H0.text: Resistance is the property that a narrow wire has more of than a wide wire when considering electrical current.

H1.text: Voltage is the property that a narrow wire will have more of than a wide wire in relation to electrical current.

H2.text: Wattage is the property that a narrow wire has more of than a wide wire when considering electrical current.

H3.text: Current is the property that a narrow wire will have more of than a wide wire, in relation to electrical current.

A4.text: A long, thin copper wire has higher resistance than a short, thick copper wire.

A5.text: A long, thin copper wire has lower conductance than a short, thick copper wire.
